Whisk lemon juice, kosher salt, seasoned salt, and chili powder together in a bowl. Slowly drizzle in olive oil while whisking rapidly until dressing is thick and creamy. Pour hot water over bulgur in a bowl; let soak until water is absorbed and bulgur is soft, about 30 minutes. Mix parsley, tomato, green bell pepper, cucumber, green onions, and mint together in a large bowl. Add bulgur; toss to combine. Drizzle dressing over bulgur mixture; toss to coat.